    {
      "id": "9d4777bc228900794e20148c7b6010516df01b55",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2021-08-25 18:28:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI'm not really familiar with the Debian/Ubuntu build process, but it seems strange to me that the build would depend on storing/using the file from such a \"prominent\" location, and without an embedded version number, rather than just creating a tarball in /tmp or in the current working directory?\n\nOn the one hand, I dislike \"workarounds\" like this where the code prints an error message for the user to fix something, when the code could just as easily delete or rename the file itself. On the other hand, the build script shouldn't be deleting (nor storing) files from a common location, which might contain the \"pristine\" sources and will not necessarily be identical to the tarball created by the build.\n\nMy preference would be to have the build use it's own temporary tarball and ignore the \"/usr/src/lustre.tar.bz2\" file entirely, but I don't know how baked into the Debian build process that is.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d0a659626a02115286f07baee0b3f242be1cda2a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2021-08-31 05:55:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nThis change cannot be cherry-picked to master.\nPlease rebase the change locally and upload the rebased commit for review.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "16d6ff703453501c851715343c38b38504d47d5f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2021-08-31 14:40:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: -Code-Review\n\nI wonder if in debian/rules this line causes the problem:\n\ncd debian/$(SOURCE_PKG)/usr/src && tar jcf lustre.tar.bz2 modules \n\nMaybe changing it to tar to /tmp would fix this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "964497370865925d3e51a5949aec578b32fc6104",
